    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)
        System - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air tools to install EGR system nuts and bolts. EGR
                        system nuts and bolts will be damaged if installed too quickly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply a light coat of clean engine oil on bolt threads and under bolt head when installing
                        used nuts and bolts.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>EGR Cooler and Bracket - Intake Side</title>
            <figure id="f3350005145" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk17/k17015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Intake side EGR cooler assembly and high-pressure oil hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler clamp (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 70 bolt (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil hose</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para id="s0511" count="1">Loosely assemble the intake side EGR cooler, cooler bracket, and two new EGR
                    cooler clamps.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the center M10 x 70 bolt in the EGR cooler bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the intake side EGR cooler assembly on the engine while not disturbing the
                    high-pressure oil hose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two M10 x 70 bolts in the ends of the EGR cooler bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the intake manifold was removed, torque intake manifold bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="sAppB01"/>
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_154.xml" xrefid="s0609">in proper sequence</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s0609"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten three M10 x 70 bolts to standard torque.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install high-pressure oil hose conduit cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, install all EGR system components before tightening the EGR cooler
                        clamps.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pre-tighten EGR cooler clamp nuts to 8 N&#183;m (71 lbf&#183;in).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen both EGR clamp nuts two turns (720 degrees).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten EGR cooler clamp nuts to a final torque of 7 N&#183;m (60 lbf&#183;in).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
